# Rust build output
/target
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb
*.tmp
# Cargo.lock is committed: the workspace ships bins (libarchive_oxide-cli), and the
# exact dependency graph is part of the reproducible build.

# cargo-fuzz build output. `fuzz/` is its own workspace (see fuzz/Cargo.toml) and has
# its own .gitignore; these root-anchored entries keep `reuse lint` (which reads this
# file) in agreement with git about what is generated. The curated `fuzz/corpus/`
# seeds are committed on purpose and are NOT ignored.
/fuzz/target/
/fuzz/artifacts/
/fuzz/coverage/

# cargo-mutants working output. Root-anchored and trailing-slash-free so ad-hoc sweep
# dirs (mutants-ll-full/) AND their console logs (mutants-ll-c2.log) are both ignored,
# without catching tracked workflow files.
/mutants.out/
/mutants.out.old/
/mutants-*

# mise local overrides (per-developer, never committed)
/mise.local.toml
/.mise.local.toml

# Editor / OS
/.idea/
/.vscode/
*.swp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.claude/
